Let's get the details with our

17:50.270 --> 17:52.150
business correspondent in Singapore,

17:52.510 --> 17:54.250
Katie Silva. Katie, what are we

17:54.250 --> 17:54.570
seeing?

17:55.670 --> 17:57.530
Well, yeah, as you mentioned, many

17:57.530 --> 17:59.350
airlines canceling flights. The likes,

17:59.450 --> 18:01.410
for example, of American Airlines, Air

18:01.410 --> 18:03.470
France, Lufthansa, Emirates and Ryan

18:03.470 --> 18:05.590
Air all canceled journeys. British

18:05.590 --> 18:07.410
Airways, for its part, told the BBC

18:07.410 --> 18:09.230
that it's only canceled one flight

18:09.230 --> 18:11.470
on Sunday and that it's going to be

18:11.470 --> 18:13.310
adjusting departure times for flights

18:13.310 --> 18:14.350
in the coming days. And that's

18:14.350 --> 18:15.790
unclear if that's because of

18:16.210 --> 18:17.750
disruption at the airport or if

18:17.750 --> 18:19.510
perhaps they want to land at

18:19.510 --> 18:20.610
different times of the day that may

18:20.610 --> 18:22.670
be deemed safer. Many of these

18:22.670 --> 18:23.790
airlines are also offering

18:24.490 --> 18:26.410
passengers to cancel their flights

18:26.410 --> 18:28.630
or to move the dates with no

18:28.630 --> 18:29.630
sort of change fees.

