Flights to Israel's second international

18:32.310 --> 18:34.330
airport, Eliat, which is a tourist

18:34.330 --> 18:35.350
destination on the Red Sea, they've

18:35.350 --> 18:37.090
been unaffected. But we've also heard

18:37.090 --> 18:39.410
that Israel's flag carrier, El Al,

18:39.590 --> 18:40.570
it's said that it's going to be

18:40.570 --> 18:42.130
maintaining its flights to Tel Aviv

18:42.130 --> 18:44.590
for now, but again allowing airlines

18:44.590 --> 18:47.250
and passengers to change their

18:47.250 --> 18:48.850
flights. But Katie, this also

18:48.850 --> 18:50.350
comes at the same time as many

18:50.350 --> 18:52.550
Israelis are trying or desperately

18:52.550 --> 18:53.790
trying to leave.

18:55.050 --> 18:57.210
Oh, to leave as well as to get

18:57.210 --> 18:58.330
home. So that's one of the major

18:58.330 --> 18:59.770
issues is that many have found

18:59.770 --> 19:01.690
themselves stranded and with fears

19:01.690 --> 19:04.190
about whether or not the

19:04.190 --> 19:05.810
airspace will be closed.

19:06.190 --> 19:07.530
So one of our reporters, for example,

19:07.530 --> 19:09.250
was actually there amongst them

19:09.250 --> 19:10.990
stranded in Cyprus, at Lanica

19:10.990 --> 19:13.050
International Airport late last night.

19:13.570 --> 19:15.230
Hundreds were packing in, hundreds of

19:15.230 --> 19:16.730
Israelis hoping to get one of the

19:16.730 --> 19:18.710
last flights home. As I say,

19:18.710 --> 19:20.270
there are still rumours about whether or not

19:20.270 --> 19:22.050
the country may close its airspace.

19:22.390 --> 19:24.050
It was hard to get tickets, we understand.

19:24.210 --> 19:26.030
Dozens were waiting to get the seats, for

19:26.030 --> 19:27.570
example, for no shows on the fully

19:27.570 --> 19:29.670
booked flights and getting back into the

19:29.670 --> 19:31.230
country certainly hasn't been easy.

19:31.610 --> 19:33.610
In terms of leaving the country, we've heard, for example,

19:33.750 --> 19:35.750
as well from Athens, the foreign

19:35.750 --> 19:38.150
ministry saying that it's working to repatriate

19:38.150 --> 19:40.110
about 149 Greek tourists

19:40.110 --> 19:41.990
from Israel. Some of them were

19:41.990 --> 19:43.930
due to arrive back late last night

19:43.930 --> 19:46.710
into Greece. But there is

19:46.710 --> 19:48.850
concern about many of the foreign

19:48.850 --> 19:50.790
workers in Israel. I know, for example, Thailand

19:50.790 --> 19:52.850
has about 30,000 workers

19:52.850 --> 19:54.750
in Israel and so governments around

19:54.750 --> 19:56.690
the world looking at how they can get their citizens home

19:56.690 --> 19:58.290
if indeed they want to leave Israel.

19:59.290 --> 20:00.750
Alright, Katie Silva, always a pleasure

20:00.750 --> 20:02.670
to have you on the program, our business

20:02.670 --> 20:04.450
correspondent there in Singapore.

20:04.770 --> 20:06.750
And we are remaining with this

20:06.750 --> 20:08.570
story and we are now going to speak to

20:08.570 --> 20:11.070
our international editor, Jeremy Bowen.

20:11.130 --> 20:12.410
Good morning to you, Jeremy.

20:12.510 --> 20:15.010
Now, you have called this a major

20:15.010 --> 20:17.570
Middle East crisis. Can you elaborate

20:17.570 --> 20:18.930
that for us, please, if you may?

20:20.170 --> 20:21.150
Well, it's

20:21.150 --> 20:22.990
unprecedented that

20:22.990 --> 20:24.550
the Palestinian

20:24.550 --> 20:27.250
armed group, Hamas, has

20:27.250 --> 20:29.390
been able to break out of Gaza,

20:29.570 --> 20:31.190
which is surrounded

20:31.190 --> 20:33.010
by, if you like, a ring of steel,

20:33.290 --> 20:35.200
of fences, wire fences and concrete,

20:36.090 --> 20:36.990
break out

20:36.990 --> 20:39.230
and kill huge

20:39.230 --> 20:40.950
numbers of Israelis,

20:41.050 --> 20:42.890
including many, many civilians.

20:42.890 --> 20:44.670
That kind of thing

20:44.670 --> 20:47.090
is something that Israel hasn't experienced

20:47.090 --> 20:48.790
before and

20:48.790 --> 20:50.450
it's becoming

20:50.450 --> 20:52.690
clear that it's a national

20:52.690 --> 20:55.330
trauma and plenty of people here

20:55.330 --> 20:56.870
compare it to the 9-11

20:56.870 --> 20:58.730
attacks in the United States.

20:59.150 --> 21:01.010
There's even one article

21:01.010 --> 21:02.630
in one of the newspapers here saying that

21:02.630 --> 21:05.010
if you adjust the death toll for population

21:05.010 --> 21:06.770
it's the equivalent of the Americans

21:06.770 --> 21:08.790
losing more than 20,000

21:08.790 --> 21:11.110
on 9-11. So, it's

21:11.110 --> 21:13.470
a big, big event

21:13.470 --> 21:15.350
and the Israeli response,

21:15.370 --> 21:17.430
which is going to be, is already

21:17.430 --> 21:19.070
very heavy military action,

21:19.330 --> 21:21.270
but they think there will be a

21:21.270 --> 21:22.690
land invasion, too, of Gaza.

21:23.450 --> 21:25.250
Now, that also is something

21:25.250 --> 21:27.350
that could have reverberations right

21:27.350 --> 21:29.110
across the region. So,

21:29.210 --> 21:31.170
we're into really unexplored

21:31.170 --> 21:32.190
territory right now.

21:33.550 --> 21:35.190
And, Jeremy, you have been in

21:35.190 --> 21:36.790
the region, you have been in the area.

21:36.910 --> 21:39.270
Just for our listeners' benefit, can you

21:39.270 --> 21:41.410
describe what Gaza Strip looks like

21:41.410 --> 21:43.210
and how that area is to

21:43.210 --> 21:43.910
Israel?

21:46.630 --> 21:47.450
Gaza is

21:47.450 --> 21:49.410
a narrow strip of land

21:49.830 --> 21:51.430
along the Mediterranean

21:51.430 --> 21:53.630
coast, which is surrounded

21:53.630 --> 21:55.150
mostly by Israel,

21:55.630 --> 21:57.370
but with

21:57.370 --> 21:59.230
a narrow border

21:59.230 --> 22:01.090
which also goes into

22:01.090 --> 22:01.690
Egypt.

22:04.190 --> 22:05.210
The Palestinian

22:05.210 --> 22:07.610
population of Gaza is around 2.4

22:07.610 --> 22:09.190
million people,

22:09.490 --> 22:11.610
many of them are descendants of

22:12.190 --> 22:13.590
families who lost their

22:13.590 --> 22:15.510
homes when Israel was created

22:15.510 --> 22:17.130
in 1948,

22:17.510 --> 22:19.750
a time that the Palestinians call the Nakba,

22:20.070 --> 22:20.990
the catastrophe.

22:22.070 --> 22:23.850
And it's an area where people

22:23.850 --> 22:25.370
are mostly very poor,

22:25.490 --> 22:27.550
they live in very difficult and

22:27.550 --> 22:29.630
cramped conditions, they're

22:29.630 --> 22:31.830
mostly not allowed to leave the area.

22:32.330 --> 22:33.610
There are plenty of

22:33.610 --> 22:35.850
adults there who've never left.

22:35.850 --> 22:37.350
And so

22:37.350 --> 22:39.770
it is a situation

22:40.490 --> 22:41.910
which is... life

22:41.910 --> 22:44.230
there is very hard and it's highly nationalistic

22:44.230 --> 22:45.890
and since 2007

22:45.890 --> 22:48.050
it's been controlled by the Palestinian

22:48.470 --> 22:49.970
militant group, Hamas,

22:50.070 --> 22:52.010
which is an Arabic acronym

22:52.010 --> 22:53.730
for the Islamic resistance movement.

22:54.450 --> 22:55.850
And you wrote a

22:56.510 --> 22:57.930
nice read on our website

22:57.930 --> 22:59.550
where you said that, you know, Hamas

22:59.550 --> 23:01.890
blindsided Israel with what you

23:01.890 --> 23:03.850
call the most serious attack in a

23:03.850 --> 23:06.170
generation. And we're hearing stories

23:06.170 --> 23:07.870
of hostages that have been taken

23:07.870 --> 23:10.130
including civilians as well as soldiers.

23:10.590 --> 23:12.110
What sort of challenge does

23:12.110 --> 23:13.930
this pose for the government of Mr.

23:14.030 --> 23:15.970
Netanyahu and the army going forward?

23:17.110 --> 23:18.230
It's the most profound

23:18.230 --> 23:19.990
challenge that any Israel government

23:19.990 --> 23:21.810
has, I think, faced probably

23:21.810 --> 23:23.910
for 50 years since

23:23.910 --> 23:26.050
the 1973 Middle East War.

23:27.850 --> 23:30.070
He is... his political enemies

23:30.070 --> 23:31.910
are already blaming him, saying

23:31.910 --> 23:34.390
that he took his arm off the ball

23:34.390 --> 23:36.110
for a variety of reasons.

23:36.850 --> 23:37.910
It's clear that there's

23:37.910 --> 23:40.010
been, from the Israeli perspective, a huge

23:40.010 --> 23:41.150
intelligence failure.

23:41.730 --> 23:44.010
And they're struggling militarily to assert

23:44.010 --> 23:45.990
themselves. They will succeed in

23:45.990 --> 23:47.770
doing that, I'm pretty certain,

23:47.790 --> 23:49.730
because Israel has got very powerful

23:49.730 --> 23:52.030
armed forces. I think the big

23:52.030 --> 23:54.130
question, which was

23:54.130 --> 23:55.610
and this is

23:56.390 --> 23:58.090
probably an equal challenge

23:58.090 --> 23:59.470
for the Israelis,

23:59.470 --> 24:02.250
is what happens after that?

24:02.430 --> 24:03.470
How do they...

24:04.450 --> 24:05.590
what happens in Gaza

24:05.590 --> 24:07.490
on the day that they leave?

24:07.570 --> 24:09.690
Because the Israelis, who used to

24:09.690 --> 24:11.490
occupy Gaza, and

24:11.490 --> 24:13.470
finally pulled out in 2005,

24:15.450 --> 24:17.690
do not want to get back into a full scale

24:17.690 --> 24:19.790
occupation. But if they send in their troops,

24:20.530 --> 24:21.650
there's going to have to be

24:21.650 --> 24:22.930
some kind of governance

24:23.430 --> 24:25.670
of a territory, which is maybe

24:25.670 --> 24:27.010
small, but as I said,

24:28.310 --> 24:29.290
contains getting on

24:29.290 --> 24:30.830
for two and a half million people.

